  "text": "It has previously been reported that binding of mAb 2G12 requires gp120 Env N-linked glycan at positions N286, N323, and N330 [CITATION_1] . Since native deglycosylation with PNGase F is not complete, and the maximally deglycosylated JRFL gp140 Env (treated with 500 U PNGase F per mg of Env) bound to DC-SIGN transfected 293T cells, we asked if 500 U PNGase F-deglycosylated gp140 could also bind the anti-gp120 carbohydratedependent mAb 2G12.",
